 * Path compression: When finding the root $r$ of $i$, we update $dist[i]$ to be the XOR sum from $i$ to $r$.
 * If $p = parent[i]$, and we find $r = root(p)$, the new $dist[i]$ is $dist[i] \oplus dist[p]$.
